Rating: 3
My new favorite soup after juicing it up a bit. I added 3 chicken boullion cubes, tripled the curry powder and used 9 ounces of spinach instead of 4 and it's probably the best soup I've ever made. Very comforting on a cold evening. I even ate it for breakfast! I also used full-fat homemade yogurt.

Rating: 3
i agree with the other reviewers. substitute chicken broth for water, use at least 2.5 tsps of high quality curry powder. also, i only used one cup of milk instead of 2. next time i think i'll use 1/2 or 3/4 cup of half and half.

Rating: 0
I'm not rating this, because I tinkered with it extensively. As per the suggestions in the reviews, I used chicken broth instead of water, tripled the curry powder, and added garam masala. I also added a clove of garlic, some fresh diced ginger, and the juice of a lime. The biggest change I made was the addition of some firm tofu, cubed and drained, after I pureed the soup. The result was very good -- like a lower-calorie, more liquid version of saag paneer, with an appealing bright, sprightly flavor. If the recipe had been written with the changes I made, I'd be giving it four forks. Also it is very good for you.

