Rating: 3
I served this at a dinner party and everyone asked for the recipe. I did make a few changes though. I added 1 vegetable boullion cube to the water, used 2% milk, and added some cayenne pepper and a little more fresh ground black pepper. I also used the entire 6 oz bag of spinach and it was very good.

Rating: 2
I found I could be very liberal with the curry powder - recipe lists a minimal amount. Also, be careful not to over-blend. I pureed mine too much and it had a very watery consistency.

Rating: 4
This soup is very easy to make and was so good that everyone who had it asked for more AND asked for the recipe. My one comment is that I thought it lacked a little zip (perhaps my curry was a touch old.) I added a little Cayenne Pepper and some tumeric to spice it up a touch. Also salt and lots of fresh ground black pepper.